				 Basu for CRPF
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Calcutta, Nov. 1: Jyoti Basu today voiced support for chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjees move to deploy central forces in Nandigram.																								Its good. The Opposition is also demanding the same, Basu said, referring to Mamata Banerjees call for central intervention to stop the bloody land war that has been going on for the last 11 months.																								The CPM patriarch also had a salve for the Left Front allies opposing the deployment of the CRPF in Nandigram. Basu endorsed their demand for a front meeting to discuss the political fallout of the move before implementing it. Yes, everything should be discussed in the Left Front, he said. 																								The RSP, Forward Bloc and the CPI have complained that neither the state cabinet nor the front was consulted before the March 14 police crackdown that claimed 14 lives. 																								CPM general secretary Prakash Karat, who was in Calcutta to attend some party programmes today, refused to comment on either Nandigram or the move to engage the CRPF. 																								CPM sources, however, said he discussed with the state party leadership the volatile situation in the land-war zone and cautioned against a repeat of March 14. 
